label.value: Lymphoma by Ann Arbor Stage

value.value: An anatomic stage for Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphomas  based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.

label.value: Calcium-Binding Domain

value.value: Many calcium-binding proteins belong to the same evolutionary family and share a type of calcium-binding domain known as the EF-hand. This type of domain consists of a twelve residue loop flanked on both side by a twelve residue alpha-helical domain. In an EF-hand loop the calcium ion is coordinated in a pentagonal bipyramidal configuration. The six residues involved in the binding are in positions 1, 3, 5, 7, 9 and 12; these residues are denoted by X, Y, Z, -Y, -X and -Z. The invariant Glu or Asp at position 12 provides two oxygens for liganding Ca (bidentate ligand). (From InterPro IPR002048)

label.value: Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma by Ann Arbor Stage

label.value: Hodgkin Lymphoma by Ann Arbor Stage

value.value: An anatomic stage for Hodgkin lymphomas based on the Ann Arbor classification criteria.

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome by AJCC v7 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of mycosis fungoides and Sezary syndrome, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides by AJCC v7 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of mycosis fungoides, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Immune Checkpoint Modulator

value.value: Any agent that modulates the immune checkpoint pathway, either by blocking any inhibitory immune checkpoint protein or by activating any stimulatory immune checkpoint protein.

label.value: Anti-ICOS Monoclonal Antibody

value.value: Any monoclonal antibody that is directed against inducible T-cell co-stimulator (ICOS; CD278).

label.value: Anti-TIM-3 Monoclonal Antibody

value.value: Any monoclonal antibody that targets the inhibitory T-cell receptor T-cell immunoglobulin and mucin domain-containing protein 3 (TIM-3; TIM3; hepatitis A virus cellular receptor 2; HAVCR2).

label.value: Lugano Stage

value.value: An adult non-Hodgkin lymphoma and adult and childhood Hodgkin lymphoma stage defined according to the Lugano classification criteria.

label.value: Lugano Classification Adult Lymphoma by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A staging system for adult Hodgkin and adult non-Hodgkin lymphomas based on the Lugano classification criteria. This staging system does not apply to ocular adnexal lymphomas (are staged according to the classification for ocular adnexal lymphoma), pediatric lymphomas (are staged according to the classification for pediatric lymphoma), primary cutaneous lymphomas (are staged according to the classification for primary cutaneous lymphoma), and multiple myelomas (are staged according to the classification for plasma cell myeloma). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Limited Stage Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Limited stage adult lymphoma based on the Lugano classification criteria. It includes stages I, IE, II, and IIE. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 3q

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage I Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I: Involvement of a single lymphatic site (i.e., nodal region, Waldeyer's ring, thymus, or spleen). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage IE Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IE: Single extralymphatic site in the absence of nodal involvement (rare in Hodgkin lymphoma). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage II Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II: Involvement of two or more lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage IIE Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIE: Contiguous extralymphatic extension from a nodal site with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage II Bulky Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II Bulky: Stage II with disease bulk. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Advanced Stage Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Advanced stage adult lymphoma based on the Lugano classification criteria. It includes stages III and IV. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage III Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm; nodes above the diaphragm with spleen involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Stage IV Adult Lymphoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV: Diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extralymphatic organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement; or noncontiguous extralymphatic organ involvement in conjunction with nodal stage II disease; or any extralymphatic organ involvement in nodal stage III disease. Stage IV includes any involvement of the CSF, bone marrow, liver, or lungs (other than by direct extension in stage IIE disease). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Lugano Classification Adult Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A staging system for adult non-Hodgkin lymphomas based on the Lugano classification criteria. This staging system does not apply to ocular adnexal lymphomas (are staged according to the classification for ocular adnexal lymphoma), pediatric non-Hodgkin lymphomas (are staged according to the St. Jude Children's Research Hospital staging system), primary cutaneous lymphomas (are staged according to the classification for primary cutaneous lymphoma), and multiple myelomas (are staged according to the classification for plasma cell myeloma). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
